items.name: Alternative History
items.title: Alternative History
items.headline: Alternative History Wiki
items.desc:
Alternate History (sometimes abbreviated AH) is the most frequently used term for the fictional genre which often presupposes a change of a minor historical event that produces an incredible series of changes in the world, diverging it from Our Timeline (OTL) and creating a new, alternate and parallel world.

Here you can create your own Alternate History story, timeline, or add to other existing historical settings. You can start one from the ground up, or add to our many existing variations right down to maps, timelines, and even events.

items.name: Implausable Alternate History Wiki
items.title: Implausable Alternate History Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the- ‘Implausible’ Alternate History Wiki! :-)!
items.desc:
An alternate history says, it may not have happened, but it could have. 100% reality may be fun, but as long it sounds believable, then reality can get frayed at the edges,  but not go ridiculous or gone. ASB, here. There are several timelines and a couple of old map games. :-)!

Many people claim that if it didn’t happen, it couldn’t happen, or that if it had certain things they would always stay that way for a person, peoples's, or nation's history, even if certain developments change the entire time frame forever, that no matter what, they are stuck with those problems for eternity. Things would always change, even slightly, someone who was important died, or someone who died didn't die. Different outcomes of battles, a storm here and there, someone build a colony here instead of there.

It would have been different if even something minor changed with a unlucky accident killing Sir Winston Churchill as a child and/or Adolph Hitler unexpectedly dying in a battle on the Fields of Flanders. 

People think that if you lost, you were born to lose, even if one inch forward could have made you win. Well things are not always like that, and I don’t think they always have. Yes, some people have been destined to lose a fight, like Japan against the nuke, they were gonna lose no matter what after the US got the atomic bomb, but if one of those scientists had been absent one or two days, America might never have had the bomb in time, and been forced to sign a conditional peace treaty with Japan.

It isn’t just about Japan in WW2, or Japan at all, its about alternate history itself, that's what alternate history means, it may not have happened, but it could have.

Let's make Alternate History more enjoyable for newcomers to the art of writing timelines, making maps, flags, Coat of Arms, map games and other things necessary to Alternate History. 

Here you can set up any map game you like providing it’s plausible that any one can join in with an existing one. Let's have fun.

items.name: Cities of History Wiki
items.title: Cities of History Wiki
items.headline: Learn all about Cities of History and get interested!
items.desc:
Basically CoHi (Always written with an i to avoid confusion with Company of Heroes) is a CityBuilder set in the beautiful land of Locany, during 3000 years; 5 Eras. Land on the shores as a Greek leader, and settle. Fight for territories as Romans. Wear off the Germans, Franks and Celts in the 8th century. See your city rise in the last days of the Medieval Era. See your trade grow as a Persian or a Chinese, to name a few. Go Imperial with palaces covered in gold, and cover them with smog from your steam vehicles and factories. Prepare to enter the Connectivity Era and see global peace, commercial space flights and green utopias.

In Cities of History, it's about two things; a happy life for your people, and you being proud of your rule over many cities. Your people need you and will be honest to admit it when they 'need' something. Satisfaction goes into great detail, as specific as 'taking this train or another, which one will get me faster to Cannisley?'. And you'll notice it when they are happy: you'll rest from their restful creek trough town, and with headphones on, you'll relax when listening to the soft music and a warming campfire. Your Japanese village at night, or your Alpine village (with that yodeling fat guy, you should've taken away his Laudelstrüßen beer.) are places you'll remember. Yes, about you. CoHi's got that feel that'll make you remember things. Maybe not the graphics, but probably the magic of Locany, the so-secret land you and i may not know. Maybe you'll like the trading partners, or maybe you'll be entertained by the humorous, and slightly satirical undertone that CoHi has. 

Maybe it's not your kind of game, but you can't be sure until you take a look at it...

Cities of History - It's about time.

items.headline: Ahistory Wiki - The new alternate history
items.desc:
What is Ahistory Wiki? It is the new wiki based around the idea of alternate history and ahistory. But, to understand what our wiki is about, you need to understand what Ahistory is; essentially, it is the complete lack of historical knowledge, or complete disregard for historical context. So in short, Ahistory is the essentially changing history on a whim; change what you would want, or not want, and the world is yours. 

This wiki will allow any user to create, edit, and change any timeline or page dedicated to alternate history or Ahistory, and let the user change what they wish. So come help out our new wiki, and I hope every will join in.

Do as you feel necessary. No unfair banning on this wiki ;), that isn't how we operate. I will check any bans possible to make sure they are fair. Alternate history or alternative history (British English), sometimes abbreviated as AH or Althist, is a genre of fiction consisting of stories in which one or more historical events occur differently from reality. These stories usually contain "what if" scenarios at crucial points in history and present an outcome of events alternative to historical record Alternate history is a way of making a theoretical timeline that encompasses different events then our own. Start making your time lines here.
